definition.value: A member of the class of pyrazoles that is 1H-pyrazole substituted by 6-methylpyridin-2-yl and 1,5-naphthyridin-2-yl groups at positions 3 and 4, respectively. It is a potent and selective inhibitor of TGF-beta R1 kinase (IC50 = 4 nM) and ALK5 autophosphorylation and binding (IC50 = 23 nM).

A member of the class of oxindoles that is 1,3-dihydro-2H-indol-2-one substituted by {3,5-dimethyl-4-[(4-methylpiperazin-1-yl)carbonyl]-1H-pyrrol-2-yl}methylidene and N-(3-chlorophenyl)-N-methylmethanesulfonyl groups at positions 3 and 5, respectively. It is a potent ATP-competitive inhibitor of c-Met (IC50 = 20 nM) and exhibits antineoplastic activity.
